OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F413A1772733966
OL,3,CMemorial flights to mark 90 years
OL,4,Csince first spitfire flight
OL,6,FTo mark 90 years since the first
OL,7,Fflight of the Spitfire, one of the
OL,8,Ficonic aircrafts is being flown from
OL,9,Fwhere the first flight took place in
OL,10,FSouthampton.
OL,12,FOn March 5, 1936, Captain Joseph
OL,13,F'Mutt' Summers climbed into the
OL,14,Fcockpit of K5054, a Supermarine Type
OL,15,F300, the prototype of the Spitfire,
OL,16,Fthe name by which the fighter plane
OL,17,Fbecame known the world over.
OL,19,FThe flight lasted just eight minutes
OL,20,Fand on landing Summers was reported to
OL,21,Fhave stated: "Don't change a thing."
OL,26,@}D@NOU}D@dO]
